@node jwt.lua
@appendixsec jwt.lua
This is the implementation of @file{jwt.lua} module,
used in examples in @ref{LuaMatch}.  It provides the following
methods:

@deffn {jwt} parse input
Parse @var{input} and build a new @acronym{JWT} object on success.
Return two values: the resulting object, and error message (on
failure).
@end deffn

@deffn {jwt} new payload secret
Create a new @acronym{JWT} object from @var{payload} and encrypt it
with the supplied @var{secret}.
@end deffn

The @acronym{JWT} object returned by either of these functions has two
methods:

@defmethod {jwt} sign secret
Sign the object using @var{secret}.  Return the signed string suitable
for use in @code{Authorization:} HTTP header.
@end defmethod

@defmethod {jwt} verify secret
The reverse operation: verify if the signature of the object returned
by @code{parse} matches @var{secret}.  Return @code{true} if it does
and @code{false} otherwise.
@end defmethod

The fields of a @acronym{JWT} object are:

@defcv {object field} jwt header
Header part of @acronym{JWT}, decoded into Lua table.
@end defcv

@defcv {object field} jwt payload
Payload part, decoded into Lua table.
@end defcv

@defcv {object field} jwt signature
Signature part, as a string.
@end defcv

@defcv {object field} jwt raw
A table containing original (undecoded) values of the three parts in
its fields @code{header}, @code{payload}, and @code{signature}.
@end defcv

